1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,145
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,095 --> 00:00:11,399
First, you do a warm-up: You practise two quick taps on the mouse while keeping the hand still.

3
00:00:11,399 --> 00:00:15,951
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

4
00:00:15,951 --> 00:00:22,907
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Open Documents, close it, then open it again.

5
00:00:22,907 --> 00:00:26,182
Repeat with staff fading prompts each time.

6
00:00:26,182 --> 00:00:32,567
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type the action we use to open an icon.

7
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:38,355
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Staff will name the target only.

8
00:00:38,355 --> 00:00:43,274
You attempts the double-click without hand-over-hand support unless needed.

9
00:00:43,274 --> 00:00:45,825
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:45,825 --> 00:00:50,380
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

